# Safety, Security & Verification

## Security
- Never read, print, edit, or commit `.env` files or secrets.
- Use Doctrine parameters; never concatenate untrusted input into DQL or SQL.
- Preserve Twig auto-escaping; use CSRF protection for state-changing web forms.
- Validate uploads by MIME/content, size, storage name/location, visibility, and authorization.
- Constrain user-influenced HttpClient destinations to prevent SSRF.
- Protect Serializer/API Platform write and read fields from privilege or sensitive-data exposure.
- Use typed, trusted Messenger payloads and avoid unsafe deserialization.
- Avoid `eval`, unsafe `unserialize`, and dynamic includes of untrusted paths.
- Do not introduce OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities.

## Git Safety
- Never skip hooks with `--no-verify`.
- Never force-push, hard-reset, or drop database tables without explicit user consent.
- Never overwrite unrelated user changes.

## Verification (Definition of Done)
- Run applicable checks from `.cursor/DOD.md` before claiming completion.
- Run tests, formatting/lint, and static analysis when the tooling exists.
- Never claim completion with failing tests, static analysis, container, route, schema, or known entry-point checks.
- Report unavailable tooling as `N/A - tooling not configured`; do not install tooling without user approval.
- Include verification evidence in the final Context Summary for implementation work.

## File Naming
- Prefix generated task/spec markdown with the skill name: `{skill-name}-{purpose}.md`.
- Use zero-padded task directories (`TASK-001/`); place temporary task docs in `tasks/TASK-{N}/` and living specs in `specs/`.
